WEBVTT

00:06.629 --> 00:14.761
The plan was particularly effective and accepted 
by the vast majority of the people in the city. And

00:15.983 --> 00:29.823
not only that, whenever we had a bond issue and it 
was known that the bond issue was in accordance

00:15.983 --> 00:29.823
with the plan, it passed overwhelmingly. And 
every time We approached a state or federal

00:33.308 --> 00:37.974
agency. We showed them the plan, showed them what 
the city was doing, and then outlined the part that

00:39.897 --> 00:53.055
we thought that particular agency should be 
responsible for. And invariably, we came away

00:57.372 --> 01:06.942
with the acceptance of the agency of our request 
and they granted the request and they followed the

00:57.372 --> 01:06.942
plan. So the plan was followed very 
conscientiously from the very beginning. The

01:13.389 --> 01:22.659
only thing that was not done was the community 
would not accept urban renewal. So the plan was

01:22.679 --> 01:26.923
implemented

01:28.051 --> 01:38.465
financed

01:28.051 --> 01:38.465
with all the different agencies participating.

01:46.977 --> 01:57.552
The Area Development Committee decided in 1949 
and 1950

01:46.977 --> 01:57.552
to proceed with the plan. It took three years to 
complete the plan, and it was published in 1953.

02:03.655 --> 02:17.327
The

02:03.655 --> 02:17.327
plan was

02:03.655 --> 02:17.327
virtually completed in the early 1960s. All of the 
proposals had been accomplished

02:18.208 --> 02:28.517
in the early 1960s. And so the Area Development 
Committee, which remained active the full time,

02:29.442 --> 02:50.927
decided that an update of the plan was needed, that 
they needed new goals and objectives. So they went

02:52.489 --> 02:55.973
back again to the Bartholomew Organization, and 
asked them to update the plan. That

03:01.646 --> 03:15.886
firm went to work and completed their plan and 
submitted the final report in December 1967. The

03:16.066 --> 03:24.778
second plan was technically very well done. The 
goals and objectives were not as clear as in the

03:30.173 --> 03:38.921
original plan. That

03:38.961 --> 03:50.371
plan is still being used as a guide. And a number of 
the things have been accomplished. one of which

03:56.990 --> 04:16.778
was Corpus Christi Beach, or North Beach, the area 
north of the ship channel

03:56.990 --> 04:16.778
to Nueces and

03:56.990 --> 04:16.778
Nueces Bay.

04:21.324 --> 04:25.410
A request was made to the Corps of Engineers to 
restore the beach. A great deal of

04:27.128 --> 04:43.969
demolition of substandard dwellings, Corpus 
Christi's own version of urban renewal without

04:27.128 --> 04:43.969
federal assistance, was undertaken. And a great 
many of the substandard housing that existed on

04:44.049 --> 04:50.037
that beach was eliminated.

04:53.140 --> 04:56.865
An act was secured. through Congress for the use of 
the Beach Erosion Act to restore the sand beach in

04:57.368 --> 05:19.277
this area that had eroded back to and even under 
some of the buildings. It took 10 years of constant

05:21.680 --> 05:25.485
effort to get this plan

05:27.457 --> 05:37.167
completed and implemented through the Corps of 
Engineers. The

05:39.249 --> 05:54.865
restoration of the beach was accomplished in 
about 1978 or 1979.

05:58.473 --> 06:27.788
Another one of the objectives was the 
construction of a dam, another water supply,

05:58.473 --> 06:27.788
because the lake at Mathis had a limited capacity 
and could not accommodate the expanding

05:58.473 --> 06:27.788
industrial and domestic demand

05:58.473 --> 06:27.788
for water.

06:30.755 --> 06:35.240
Controversy arose as to the location of this dam. 
The area development plan did recommend the site

06:35.260 --> 06:58.905
that is now being completed for

06:35.260 --> 06:58.905
the new dam at Cho Canyon.

07:00.083 --> 07:12.219
The dam was

07:00.083 --> 07:12.219
partially financed through the Bureau of 
Reclamation.

07:12.239 --> 07:28.420
The gates of this dam are going to be closed within 
the next two months, and this lake will furnish a

07:12.239 --> 07:28.420
water supply

07:12.239 --> 07:28.420
well into the 2020s.

07:29.800 --> 07:32.564
This is just finished now. That's just finished. 
That's another accomplishment of the plan.

